---

[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[Music] For the first time ever, a true crossover between Waverunner and boat, Yamaha introduces the all-new CrossWave, the largest, most versatile personal watercraft ever built. Designed to carry up to four passengers and everything you'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'need for a day on the water. From the moment you see it, you know this isn\'t your typical Waverunner. At just under 13 ft long and 67 in wide, the CrossWave feels bigger, bolder, more'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stable, and more capable than any other PWC on the water. The first thing you\'ll notice is the walk-around deck. Yes, it\'s the only PWC where you can actually walk all the way around the bow and stern, like it\'s your'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'own floating patio. Whether you\'re fishing, touring, or using it as a jumping-off point for the kids, the CrossWave gives you space to move with confidence, thanks in part to its unmatched stability.'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Storage? The CrossWave packs a massive 82 gallons of storage space, the most in the industry. Between the bow anchor locker, glove box, underseat storage, and dual inner hull stern storage'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'compartments. Rods, coolers, towels, snacks, bring it all. Pair that with a 26-gallon fuel tank, the largest in the industry, and you\'ve got an all-day adventure machine. At the helm, Yamaha gives you something'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'no one else does, a floating display with two 7-in touchscreens. On the left, the Yamaha Connect system with drive control, Bluetooth, and trip info. On the right, a Simrad NSS marine display'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with sonar charting and split-screen functionality. Together, they turn your dash into seamless technology and style, all at your fingertips. Every great adventure deserves a soundtrack. The CrossWave delivers dual 8-in footwell'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'speakers, the largest factory-installed audio system you\'ll find on a PWC. And because Yamaha knows you\'ll want to stay out there all day, the CrossWave comes standard with a custom 55-qt cooler. Slide it along the stern\'s'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'T-track system, reposition to fit your setup, or swap it out for even more gear when you remove the extra seat. This four-passenger Waverunner easily transforms into a two-seater when you want more open space for cargo, casting,'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'or lounging at the sandbar. Every detail supports long days on the water. Built-in pole storage, full marine mat covered deck, reboarding step, and prep for a group 24 deep-cycle'

[02:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'marine battery to power your accessories. Every CrossWave comes shipped on its own custom trailer, and that\'s a huge included value. The Yamaha CrossWave isn\'t just another PWC, it\'s a whole new way to experience'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the water. Fishing, cruising, sandbar lounging, and everything in between. It\'s the ultimate in versatility and getting the most out of your day on the water.'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[Music]'
